  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="TK14">
<l>ēri ṉuḻāa ruḻavar puyaleṉṉum</l>
<l>vāri vaḷaṅkuṉṟik kāl</l>            
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The ploughmen do no scratching with their ploughs when</l>
<l>the increase of that income known as rain wanes.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <head>Parimēlaḻakar</head>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="TK14_P1">
          (i-ḷ). uḻavar ērā ṉuḻutalaic ceyyār,maḻai yeṉṉum varuvāy taṉpayaṉ kuṉṟiṉ, (e-ṟu).
        </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">
          The meaning ... : Ploughmen will not do their ploughing with their ploughs, if the income known as rain/clouds diminishes [with respect to?] its fruit.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="TK14_P2">
          kuṉṟiyakkāleṉpatu kuṟaintuniṉṟatu. uṇaviṉmaikkuk kāraṇaṅ kūṟiyavāṟu.
        </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">
          "When it wanes" [means] its continuing to be wanting(?). [In this] way, the cause for the absence of nourishment [that was the topic of the preceding poem] has been stated.
        </p>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <head>Maṇakkuṭavar (16/17)</head>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="TK14_M1">
          (i - ḷ.) ēriṉuḻutalait tavirvāruḻavar ; puyalākiya vāriyiṉuṭaiya vaḷaṅ kuṟaintakālattu, (e - ṟu).
        </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">
          The meaning ... : The ploughmen desist from their ploughing with the plough at the time when the abundance of the profit that is rain/clouds has diminished.
        </p>
      </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="TK14_M2">
            iḵtu uḻuva rillai yeṉṟatu.
          </p>
          <p xml:lang="en">
            This [means] that there will be no ploughmen(?).
          </p>
        </div>
      </body>
    </text>
